      • getLineSourceForArgument

        public static LineSource getLineSourceForArgument(java.lang.String argName,
                                                  java.lang.String arg,
                                                  boolean useStdIn)
        Identifies the type of file or directory (or none) given as an argument and provides the appropriate LineSource for it. Optionally opens stdin if arg is null.


        Note that Dagger does not allow for any provider and thus neither any constructor used in this provider to throw an exception. For that reason errors are output to stderr, and most of the constructors for these word sources try to catch exceptions.
        Parameters:
        argName - the name of the argument specifying the source
        arg - the string path provided as an argument for the source
        useStdIn - if arg is null true if should we read stdin
        Returns:
        a file, directory or input LineSource depending on arguments
